# The Mateus Personal Website & Archive

> Technical portfolio and interactive repository developed under the Frutiger Aero design framework.

---

## About The Project

This project is a web platform designed to index personal software projects, interactive experiments, and digital archives. The application features a user interface inspired by early 2000s operating systems, leveraging glassmorphism principles and modular layouts.

> **Development Note:** Artificial Intelligence was utilized to generate and structure the code for the DVD bouncing feature in the interactive module.

### Core Features

* User interface built on Frutiger Aero design patterns, featuring semi-transparent UI elements and dynamic containers.
* Showcase section referencing external technical projects, including 3D web applications.
* Interactive module featuring an HTML5 Canvas graphic engine simulating bouncing DVD logo physics and collision detection (developed with AI assistance).
* Lightweight codebase developed using native web technologies without external framework dependencies.

---

## Technical Stack

* **HTML5:** Semantic document structure and layout hierarchy.
* **CSS3:** Modular styling, transition keyframes, and glassmorphism rendering.
* **JavaScript (ES6+):** Tab state management, DOM manipulation, and Canvas rendering loops.